Skin relatively thick, cactus-like prickles more or less covering body, in most dense region about 13 prickles in orbit length. Pyloric caeca 31–34 ( 31 ;
Burke, 1930
), length about 33–53 % HL, center-left side of visceral cavity.

Life history. Reaching a maximum size of 350 mm (
Okiyama 2004
), the largest specimen examined was 264.8 mm ( FAKU 131402 ), a ripe female with yolked eggs. The smallest ripe female with yolked eggs was 194.4 mm . Eggs were 3.6 –5.0 mm in diameter. The only ripe male was 229.2 mm .
